               <msContents>
                  <summary>Recto: power of attorney given to ʿAmram b. Joseph he-Ḥasid by Moses b. Abraham to collect what is owed to him by Maḥbūb b. Ḥubbān. Dated Adar 1395 of the Seleucid Era (= 1084 CE), Fusṭāṭ. Mentions Ḥassūn ha-Levi b. Solomon and al-Mahdiyya. Verso: post-classical piyyuṭ, אשא דעי ליחד, with an alphabetic acrostic and internal rhyme. Parts of Deuteronomy 32:4 are used in the refrain, and from strophe to strophe the first word of the line used in the previous strophe is deleted and another one added on the end.
</summary>
                  <msItem n="1">
                     <title>Legal document; piyyuṭ</title>
